[{"location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Types","page":"API Reference","title":"Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Predicates","page":"API Reference","title":"Predicates","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Measurements","page":"API Reference","title":"Measurements","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Geometry-operations","page":"API Reference","title":"Geometry operations","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Boolean-operations","page":"API Reference","title":"Boolean operations","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.S2Geog","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.S2Geog","text":"S2Geog{Trait}\n\nA wrapper around an S2GeogGeography pointer. Parameterized by GeoInterface geometry trait for type-stable dispatch.\n\nAutomatically frees the underlying C object via a finalizer.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.intersects","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.intersects","text":"intersects(geom1, geom2) -> Bool\n\nTest whether two geometries intersect (share any portion of space).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.equals","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.equals","text":"equals(geom1, geom2) -> Bool\n\nTest whether two geometries are spatially equal.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.contains","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.contains","text":"contains(geom1, geom2) -> Bool\n\nTest whether geom1 contains geom2.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.touches","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.touches","text":"touches(geom1, geom2) -> Bool\n\nTest whether two geometries touch (share a boundary but not interior).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.distance","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.distance","text":"distance(geom1, geom2) -> Float64\n\nCompute the spherical distance (in radians) between two geometries. Multiply by Earth's radius (~6371 km) to get distance in km.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.area","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.area","text":"area(geom::S2Geog) -> Float64\n\nCompute the area of a geography in steradians. Multiply by Earth's radius squared (~6371² km²) to get area in km².\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.s2_length","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.s2_length","text":"s2_length(geom::S2Geog) -> Float64\n\nCompute the length of a geography in radians (for lines/polylines). Named s2_length to avoid shadowing Base.length.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.perimeter","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.perimeter","text":"perimeter(geom::S2Geog) -> Float64\n\nCompute the perimeter of a geography in radians (for polygons).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.centroid","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.centroid","text":"centroid(geom) -> S2Geog{PointTrait}\n\nCompute the centroid of a geography.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.convex_hull","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.convex_hull","text":"convex_hull(geom) -> S2Geog{PolygonTrait}\n\nCompute the convex hull of a geography.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.boundary","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.boundary","text":"boundary(geom) -> S2Geog\n\nCompute the boundary of a geography.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.intersection","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.intersection","text":"intersection(geom1, geom2) -> S2Geog\n\nCompute the intersection of two geometries.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.s2_union","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.s2_union","text":"s2_union(geom1, geom2) -> S2Geog\n\nCompute the union of two geometries. Named s2_union to avoid shadowing Base.union.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.difference","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.difference","text":"difference(geom1, geom2) -> S2Geog\n\nCompute the difference of two geometries (part of geom1 not in geom2).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#S2Geography.sym_difference","page":"API Reference","title":"S2Geography.sym_difference","text":"sym_difference(geom1, geom2) -> S2Geog\n\nCompute the symmetric difference of two geometries.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#S2Geography.jl","page":"Home","title":"S2Geography.jl","text":"Julia bindings for s2geography, providing spherical geometry operations powered by Google's S2Geometry library.\n\nUnlike planar geometry libraries, S2Geography operates on the sphere, giving correct results for geographic data without projection artifacts.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Features","page":"Home","title":"Features","text":"Spherical geometry predicates: intersects, equals, contains, touches\nDistance, area, length, and perimeter measurements (in radians/steradians)\nGeometry operations: centroid, convex_hull, boundary\nBoolean operations: intersection, s2_union, difference, sym_difference\nFull GeoInterface.jl support","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/JuliaGeo/S2Geography.jl\")\n\nnote: Note\nThis package currently requires a locally built libs2geography_c shared library with the path available via LD_LIBRARY_PATH / DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH. A JLL package is in progress.","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Tutorial","page":"Tutorial","title":"Tutorial","text":"This tutorial shows how to use S2Geography.jl with real-world geographic data from NaturalEarth.jl.","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Loading-data","page":"Tutorial","title":"Loading data","text":"using S2Geography\nimport GeoInterface as GI\nusing NaturalEarth\n\ncountries = naturalearth(\"admin_0_countries\", 110)\nnothing # hide\n\nPick out two countries by name:\n\nnames = countries.NAME\ngermany_idx = findfirst(==(\"Germany\"), names)\nfrance_idx = findfirst(==(\"France\"), names)\n\ngermany_geom = countries.geometry[germany_idx]\nfrance_geom = countries.geometry[france_idx]\nnothing # hide","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Converting-to-S2Geog","page":"Tutorial","title":"Converting to S2Geog","text":"Any GeoInterface-compatible geometry can be converted to S2Geog:\n\ngermany = GI.convert(S2Geog, germany_geom)\nfrance = GI.convert(S2Geog, france_geom)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Spatial-predicates","page":"Tutorial","title":"Spatial predicates","text":"Test whether two countries share a border:\n\nS2Geography.intersects(germany, france)\n\nbrazil_idx = findfirst(==(\"Brazil\"), names)\nbrazil = GI.convert(S2Geog, countries.geometry[brazil_idx])\nS2Geography.intersects(germany, brazil)\n\nCheck if a point is inside a country:\n\nberlin = S2Geography._from_wkt(\"POINT (13.405 52.52)\")\nS2Geography.contains(germany, berlin)","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Measurements","page":"Tutorial","title":"Measurements","text":"Distance between two points (in radians – multiply by 6371 for km):\n\nparis = S2Geography._from_wkt(\"POINT (2.3522 48.8566)\")\nd = S2Geography.distance(berlin, paris)\nkm = d * 6371\nprintln(\"Berlin to Paris: $(round(km, digits=1)) km\")\n\nArea (in steradians – multiply by 6371^2 for km^2):\n\na = S2Geography.area(germany)\nkm2 = a * 6371^2\nprintln(\"Germany area: $(round(km2, digits=0)) km²\")","category":"section"},{"location":"tutorial/#Boolean-operations","page":"Tutorial","title":"Boolean operations","text":"Compute the intersection of two countries (their shared border region):\n\noverlap = S2Geography.intersection(germany, france)\nprintln(\"Intersection area: $(round(S2Geography.area(overlap) * 6371^2, digits=0)) km²\")\n\nCompute the centroid:\n\nc = S2Geography.centroid(germany)\nprintln(\"Germany centroid: ($(round(GI.x(c), digits=2))°, $(round(GI.y(c), digits=2))°)\")","category":"section"}]
